The paper deals with distributed graph querying, which involves partitioning the graph and processing the data in parallel across a cluster of servers. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses graph partitioning, which is a common technique used in Distributed Systems (cs.DS) and Database (cs.DB) research. The paper also mentions load balancing and fault tolerance, which are important topics in Networked Information Systems (cs.NI) and System and Information Theory (cs.SI). Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.NI, cs.SI, and cs.DC.
